It seems to me that the future of music is singles.  Only ever hearing one or two songs off each ablum.....

NEWSFLASH!!!!

everyone knows this.  nothing new here.


But something strange has happened to me lately.  I have been err... umm... downloading.. perhaps legally.... perhaps not... torrent files instead of crap of bearshare and such.  As a result it is much more difficult to find single songs... but much easier to get whole albums.. even whole catalogs of an artist in one download.
So now I find myself listening to entire albums again in their entirety... from beginning to end... something I dont do unless its a Tori or Radiohead or other such album the last few years.
So many cool songs I would have otherwise missed.... plus it reminds me of a simpler time.... when I was a kid... I listened to tapes as a whole.. couldnt just go track to track like you could with a CD.
Dave Nobles.... fraternity brother of mine.... he used to load up a few cds at parties and just let em run... I still remember 2/5th of the music every night being Eagles tunes... and not just all the radio stuff.

So... nothing else here... go home.... listen to some albums in their entirety... the way they were meant to be.. maybe find some gold in those CDs...

Ive been a fan of the Dead for years.... but until a couple months ago... I never heard American Beauty from front to back.... now thats some good shit....

Ciao.
